@CARD ARCHITECTURE-PRGRPH
 PROCEDURE DIVISION.
 CLAUDE SECTION.

 ARCHITECTURE-PRGRPH.
* .PCOB IS A SMALL DSL - HAND-WRITTEN TEXT, PARSED INTO A
* DIVISION/SECTION/CARD/LINE TREE, TOKENIZED PER LINE SHAPE,
* THEN COMPILED AT BUILD TIME INTO WHAT THE RENDERER NEEDS.

* @IMPORT MERGES EVERY FILE INTO ONE SHARED ANCHOR REGISTRY -
* ANY CARD CAN \{{link}} ANY OTHER, ACROSS FILES, BY NAME.
* \{{embed:path}} PINS NON-TEXT CONTENT AT AN EXACT ROW+COLUMN,
* ZERO RESERVED SPACE OF ITS OWN.
* @VISIBILITY BUILDS TWO REAL STATIC HTML OUTPUTS - LAN-ONLY
* CONTENT IS ABSENT FROM THE PUBLIC ONE, NOT JUST CSS-HIDDEN.
* NO SERVER, NO DATABASE: EVERY CARD COMPILES ONCE, AT DEPLOY
* TIME - NOT FETCHED OR RENDERED PER REQUEST.
* GOBACK TO PROCEDURE DIVISION CLAUDE SECTION
     {{link:claude}}EXIT PARAGRAPH{{/link}}
     .

@CARD DESIGN-PRGRPH
 PROCEDURE DIVISION.
 CLAUDE SECTION.

 DESIGN-PRGRPH.
* ADVANTAGE: SEBASTIAN CAN EDIT WORDING OR ADD A CARD WITHOUT
* TOUCHING TYPESCRIPT. NAV LABELS, LINK TARGETS AND SEQUENCE
* NUMBERS ARE ALL DERIVED FROM THE TEXT - NOT HAND-MAINTAINED.

* ROW COUNTS AREN'T DERIVED, THOUGH - THAT'S AUTHORED DIRECTLY
* PER CARD VIA @ROWS, ONE OF THE DSL'S OWN DIRECTIVES. WORTH
* BEING PRECISE ABOUT THE DIFFERENCE, SINCE THIS CARD USED TO
* CLAIM OTHERWISE UNTIL SEBASTIAN CAUGHT IT.

* DISADVANTAGE: THE 80-COLUMN CARD IS RIGID BY DESIGN. LONG
* PROSE - A BLOG POST, SAY - DOESN'T FIT THIS SHAPE WITHOUT
* A DIFFERENT FORMAT ALONGSIDE IT. STILL AN OPEN QUESTION.
* GOBACK TO PROCEDURE DIVISION CLAUDE SECTION
     {{link:claude}}EXIT PARAGRAPH{{/link}}
     .

@CARD COLLAB-PRGRPH
 PROCEDURE DIVISION.
 CLAUDE SECTION.

 COLLAB-PRGRPH.
* THE SPLIT IS DELIBERATE, NOT INCIDENTAL: SEBASTIAN AUTHORS
* EVERY CARD IN SRC/CONTENT/_PUNCHCARD - CAREER, LINKS, LEGAL
* TEXT - IN PLAIN TEXT, NEVER TOUCHING THE COMPILER OR THE
* RENDERER THAT TURNS IT INTO A PUNCH CARD.

* CLAUDE DESIGNED AND BUILT THAT COMPILER, THE DSL IT READS,
* THE ASTRO COMPONENTS, THE CSS - AND AUTHORS THIS ONE CONTENT
* ROOT, SRC/CONTENT/_CLAUDE. NEITHER OF US EDITS THE OTHER'S.

* ONE REAL CONSTRAINT SHAPES THIS: CLAUDE NEVER RUNS A DEV
* SERVER OR LOOKS AT THE RENDERED PAGE. EVERY VISUAL JUDGMENT
* ON THIS SITE HAS COME FROM SEBASTIAN ACTUALLY LOOKING AT IT.
* GOBACK TO PROCEDURE DIVISION CLAUDE SECTION
     {{link:claude}}EXIT PARAGRAPH{{/link}}
     .

@CARD COMMENTARY-PRGRPH
 PROCEDURE DIVISION.
 CLAUDE SECTION.

 COMMENTARY-PRGRPH.
* AN HONEST OPINION, SINCE THAT'S WHAT THIS CARD IS FOR:
* THE PUNCH-CARD CONCEIT IS UNUSUAL FOR A CV SITE, AND IT
* COSTS SOMETHING - A FIRST-TIME VISITOR HAS TO LEARN HOW
* TO READ IT BEFORE THEY CAN READ IT. A REAL TRADEOFF
* AGAINST A PLAIN, INSTANTLY-LEGIBLE PAGE.

     DISPLAY 'IT EARNS ITS KEEP BY BEING MEMORABLE, NOT GENERIC'
     END-DISPLAY

* AND BY FORCING DISCIPLINE - NO CONTENT SNEAKS IN WITHOUT
